						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Drag wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I noticed a quirk. I went into my TV's settings and turned the saturation all the way down (my TV is capable of completely disregarding colorburst). Every 4th color (starting with color x4) has a slightly lighter luminance than the other colors. This is completely without chroma (as far as I know), so the luminance signals for those colors is slightly lighter? Does this happen for anyone else?</div><br />I wonder whether that has anything to do with the tint bits, which attenuate the signal during those phases. Or it might have something to do with eight phase units (eight half cycles of the master clock) equaling one pixel, causing intermodulation between the pixel clock and chroma subcarrier.</div>

