					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Scaling the entire signal level by the sync pulse works well for RF because RF uses <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Broadcast_television_systems#Image_polarity" class="postlink">negative modulation</a>, where sync is the highest signal level. Composite uses positive modulation, so it's less helpful there.<br /><br />I too have been assuming that color burst is for phase.</div>

